    %title Tee Parham
  %body
    .header-wrap.outer
      %header.inner
        %h1 Tee Parham
        %h2
          Dad, idealist, gambler, kids basketball coach,
          expert amateur snowboarder, ping ponger, progressive citizen,
          code writer, product & engineering lead at Neighborland.
    .main-content-wrap.outer
      %section.main-content.inner
        %h3 I'm on the internet
        .pile
          %a{href: "https://github.com/teeparham/gemdiff", class: "icon-github"}
          %a{href: "https://www.linkedin.com/in/teeparham", class: "icon-linkedin"}
          %a{href: "https://twitter.com/teeparham", class: "icon-twitter"}
          %a{href: "http://stackoverflow.com/users/162934/tee", class: "icon-stackoverflow"}
      %section.main-content.inner
        %h3 I contribute to open source software
        %ul
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/teeparham/gemdiff"} gemdiff
            is a command-line tool to find source code for ruby gems.
            You can compare source code differences between the current version of a gem
            in your bundle and the latest version of the gem. gemdiff connects
            gem version management (rubygems + bundler) with source code (GitHub).
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/rgeo/rgeo"} rgeo
            is a geospatial data library for ruby. It wraps the GEOS and Proj C libraries
            and provides spatial types such as point, linestring, and polygon.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/rgeo/activerecord-postgis-adapter"} activerecord-postgis-adapter
            is the PostGIS ActiveRecord adapter. Use it to connect ActiveRecord models
            to your PostGIS database, with all the geometry type methods from rgeo.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/neighborland/cache_rocket"} cache_rocket
            improves fragment caching efficiency in Rails. CacheRocket allows caching
            more generic html fragments and allowing the contents of the cached fragments to be replaced with dynamic content.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/neighborland/pres"} pres
            provides simple Rails presenter modules and classes.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/neighborland/sluggi"} sluggi
            is a friendly_id-inspired slugging library for ActiveRecord models.
            Use it to build nice-looking URLs. It provides basic slugs, slug history,
            and the ability to define multiple slug candidates.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/neighborland/scopy"} scopy
            provides common ActiveRecord model scopes for common columns including
            id, created_at, and name.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/neighborland/resque_solo"} resque_solo
            ensures unique jobs in Resque.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/rgeo/rgeo-activerecord"} rgeo-activerecord
            provides RGeo ActiveRecord extensions, used by the PostGIS, MySql, and
            Spatialite database adapters.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/haml/haml"} haml
            is the HTML Abstraction Markup Language.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/teeparham/paperclip-meta"} paperclip-meta
            adds image sizes to Paperclip attachments.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/teeparham/phonely_feud"} phonely_feud
            is a weekend prototype I hacked together for the first National Day
            of Civic Hacking. It allows the anyone to lookup a suspicious phone
            number and answer "Is this phone number a scam?"
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/teeparham/cache_benchmark"} cache_benchmark
            benchmarks different Rails caching techniques.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/neighborland/mobu"} mobu
            detects device types based on the user-agent, and modifies Rails view paths
            based on the device type. This project is no longer maintained and
            you should not modify content based on the user agent if you can help it.
          %li
            %a{href: "https://github.com/teeparham/loady"} loady
            does delimited file loading and logging in ruby.
        .space
